Had a great time in St Louis with my brother @sergpro11, @krystenchapman last week! It's always good running into family and friends on the road. We walked around Gateway Arch national Park and eat at our favorite sushi spot with my brothers friends. Scroll to the last video to see how Lucy @vanlifedogs felt about Sergio leaving or maybe just not leaving her! Lol

Day 10 in Yosemite @yosemitenps and I don't want to leave anytime soon! These past two weeks have been amazing, I've gotten to climb and shoot almost everyday and have made some new awesome friends! I think this might just have to be a yearly ritual from now on! I will be spending one more week here then heading to Bend Oregon for my first van meetup! @descendonbend

I drove up the pacific coastal highway about two weeks ago and stop at my favorite little park called Swamiâ€™s Park in Encinitas California. I met a lot of surfers and was able to shoot all the surfing I wanted for days! We got every type of condition from sunny days to foggy afternoons and then ending with amazing sunsets every night. Iâ€™ll tell you one thing, chasing the surfers with the drone was a lot harder then I thought but practice makes perfect. I guess that means Iâ€™ll just have to spend more time back on this coast!

If you look hard enough you can see me in the middle of the frame stretching my arms out. Came here to watch the sunset last night and met a new friend! Thanks for the picture Mike!  It's gonna be hard to leave this place but I still have so much to see in California! On a side note someone called the cops on me because I was parked next to the red curb, by the time the cop showed up I had already found a parking spot and he was really cool about it. He was like you look like a good guy with a good dog just giving you a warning but your good have a good night. So that's exactly what I did!

Hope everyone is having a good day, week and year! It's definitely been a crazy year for me, lots of things have changed and lots of new opportunities have come into my life and I am thankful for all of them! I'm still growing and learning everyday and I want you to know that's it's ok if you don't know where your life is going at the moment. But just keep doing what your doing and everything will be alright! I'll be back in Greenville in one week and back in my van with my pup Lucy @vanlifedogs. Can't wait to catch up with family and friends while I'm in town. Hit me up if you wanna hang!
